What you need to know:

London club Fulham will now join already-demoted West Bromwich Albion and Sheffield United in the second-tier Championship next seasonFulham's defeat also meant all three relegation places were decided with at least three games to go, ensuring there would be no last-day drama in the battle to beat the dropFulham's luck ran out at the other end of the pitch in the 70th minute when Andre-Frank Zambo Anguissa's shot beat Burnley keeper Nick Pope only to bounce clear off the underside of the bar